      <title>Peak season isn’t the time to leave big &amp; bulky out of same-day</title>
      <link>https://www.roadie.com/blog/peak-season-isnt-the-time-to-leave-big-bulky-out-of-same-day</link>
      <description>&lt;div class="hs-featured-image-wrapper"&gt; 
 &lt;a href="https://www.roadie.com/blog/peak-season-isnt-the-time-to-leave-big-bulky-out-of-same-day" title="" class="hs-featured-image-link"&gt; &lt;img src="https://46302491.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/46302491/B2B%20011%20-%20Blog%20-%20An%20unpredictable%20peak%20season%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20time%20to%20leave%20big%20%26%20bulky%20out%20of%20same-day.png" alt="Peak season isn’t the time to leave big &amp;amp; bulky out of same-day" class="hs-featured-image" style="width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;"&gt; &lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Tariff unpredictability has thrown a proverbial wrench in peak season planning for 2025. Earlier this year, retailers rushed to &lt;a href="https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/tariff-timeline-peak-season-ocean-shipping-los-angeles-port/752999/"&gt;&lt;span&gt;frontload inventory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in anticipation of shifting tariff deadlines, only to face another challenge: consumer sentiment. After trending downward through much of the spring, &lt;a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/13/consumer-sentiment-reading-rebounds-to-much-higher-level-than-expected-as-people-get-over-tariff-shock.html"&gt;&lt;span&gt;demand rebounded&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; unexpectedly in June, leaving analysts and retailers alike scratching their heads. If there’s one thing retailers know about the 2025 peak season, it’s that they have to prepare for the unpredictable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;div class="hs-featured-image-wrapper"&gt; 
 &lt;a href="https://www.roadie.com/blog/peak-season-isnt-the-time-to-leave-big-bulky-out-of-same-day" title="" class="hs-featured-image-link"&gt; &lt;img src="https://46302491.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/46302491/B2B%20011%20-%20Blog%20-%20An%20unpredictable%20peak%20season%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20time%20to%20leave%20big%20%26%20bulky%20out%20of%20same-day.png" alt="Peak season isn’t the time to leave big &amp;amp; bulky out of same-day" class="hs-featured-image" style="width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;"&gt; &lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Tariff unpredictability has thrown a proverbial wrench in peak season planning for 2025. Earlier this year, retailers rushed to &lt;a href="https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/tariff-timeline-peak-season-ocean-shipping-los-angeles-port/752999/"&gt;&lt;span&gt;frontload inventory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in anticipation of shifting tariff deadlines, only to face another challenge: consumer sentiment. After trending downward through much of the spring, &lt;a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/13/consumer-sentiment-reading-rebounds-to-much-higher-level-than-expected-as-people-get-over-tariff-shock.html"&gt;&lt;span&gt;demand rebounded&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; unexpectedly in June, leaving analysts and retailers alike scratching their heads. If there’s one thing retailers know about the 2025 peak season, it’s that they have to prepare for the unpredictable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  
